##Idea

An **indexed (âˆž,1)-category** is the [[(âˆž,1)-category theory|(âˆž,1)-category theoretic]] analogue of an [[indexed category]]. If $S$ is an (âˆž,1)-category, then an indexed (âˆž,1)-category is a functor from $S^{op}$ to [[(âˆž,1)Cat]].

The [[(âˆž,1)-Grothendieck construction]] establishes an equivalence between (âˆž,1)-categories indexed by $S$ and [[Cartesian fibrations]] over $S$.

